Feature Plan: HomeVC trending carousel to list transform (UIKit only)

Objective
- Add a UIKit trending section to `HomeVC` backed by `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/trending-movies`.
- Render top 5 movies as a horizontal carousel by default.
- On swipe-down gesture, transform the carousel into a vertical list using the same in-memory data.
- In list mode, show movie description text clamped to max 3 lines.
- Apply black/white/grey visual polish with optional spacing and soft shadow refinements for a cleaner HomeVC section.

Constraints
- UIKit-only implementation (`UIViewController`, `UICollectionView`, `UITableView`, gesture recognizers).
- No SwiftUI usage for this feature.
- Backend API contract remains unchanged.

Role ownership
- Primary iOS implementation: `@ios-dev`
- Backend contract consumer parity: `@backend-dev`
- Test and regression verification: `@testing-engineer`

Target files
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/HomeVC.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/Networking/BackendServices.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/Networking/APIClient.swift` (if request model/parse helpers required)
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/homevc-trending-carousel.prototype.html`

High-level architecture
1. Networking
   - Add/confirm `MbooksService` function for trending call (`limit=5`, optional `days`).
   - Decode `trendingMovies` payload into local HomeVC-friendly model.
2. HomeVC state model
   - Introduce `TrendingDisplayMode`:
     - `carousel`
     - `list`
   - Keep one shared `trendingMovies` array to avoid duplicate fetch on mode switch.
3. Default carousel UI
   - Build horizontal `UICollectionView` (or existing card scroller) section.
   - Show poster + title.
4. Swipe-down transform
   - Add downward gesture recognizer on trending container.
   - Animate transition to list mode (crossfade/constraint transition).
5. List mode UI
   - `UITableView` rows with poster, title, description.
   - Description label `numberOfLines = 3`, truncation tail.
6. States and fallbacks
   - Loading placeholder/skeleton.
   - Empty response state.
   - Error state with non-blocking tap-to-retry interaction.
   - Placeholder image and fallback description text when endpoint description data is missing.
7. Visual style polish
   - Use a black/white/grey palette for the trending section background, text, and cards.
   - Apply optional padding/spacing tuning around section container and card/list content.
   - Apply optional soft card/container shadows with readability-first contrast.

Data contract mapping
- Source key: `trendingMovies`
- Field mapping:
  - `movieId` -> Int
  - `name` -> String
  - `thumbnail_picture` -> String
  - `large_picture` -> String
  - `bookedTickets` -> Int
  - `lastBookingTime` -> optional String
- Description source
  - If endpoint payload lacks description field, list uses fallback text.

Interaction behavior
- Initial state: `carousel`.
- Gesture: swipe down on trending section -> switch to `list`.
- Optional return interaction allowed (swipe up or toggle icon) if non-conflicting.
- Transition should preserve order and data set.

Observability and debug
- Log request start/end and item count.
- Log mode switch events (`carousel` -> `list`).
- Do not log auth/session secrets.

Verification strategy
- Manual checks in simulator/device for:
  - default carousel rendering
  - swipe-down transform
  - list description clamp to 3 lines
  - empty/error states
  - black/white/grey palette and optional spacing/shadow polish
  - stable ordering consistency across both modes
- Add automated tests in follow-up if required (UI + networking parse).

Definition of done
- HomeVC renders top-5 trending carousel from endpoint.
- Swipe down transforms to list mode with animation.
- List mode description max-lines rule enforced.
- HomeVC trending section follows black/white/grey style with optional padding/shadow polish.
- UIKit-only implementation confirmed.
- Prototype exists for design review.

